column5: A friend and I hit a splake-stocked lake the past couple of weekends, and found a new (new to us) natural brookie lake in the area.  Splake were loving EGBs in gold/black striped pattern.      Brookies were tough to nail but eventually got a nice specimen on a gold-bladed mepps.    Hoping to a hit a few more lakes before the blackflies are out in full force!
Great report and pics jayess Awesome     Now I know what a splake looks like   never seen one before!!! Leechman
